  "text": "whereV A and V T denote alveolar ventilation and tidal volume, respectively. The positive coefficients k diff,i can be estimated from experimental data, see [CITATION_1] and table A1. A primary advantage of the above treatment is that much of the temporal and spatial heterogeneity associated with highly soluble gas exchange can be captured within a unidirectional rather than a bidirectional flow framework as in [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . From an operational view, this drastically reduces the number of required model equations, thereby yielding parsimonious parameterizations as well as tractable model structures.",
